<doc id="659414" wikidata="Q2671076" url="?curid=659414" title="Information-theoretic death">
<text>Information-theoretic death is a term of art used in cryonics to define death in a way that is permanent and independent of any future medical advances, no matter how distant or improbable that may be. Because detailed reading or restoration of information-storing brain structures is beyond current technology, the term lacks practical importance in contemporary medicine.

